			<div class="content" id="post-content-913282">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Pi is an irrational number, so it's infinitely long. Even if the pattern is also infinitely long, it would show up eventually, guaranteed. Admittedly, it might take a while to find, but it would be there.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Not necessarily. You can have a pile infinite apples, each different in size and shape, but that doesn't necessarily imply you can find a orange in the pile.</p>
<p>For example, take the number:</p>
<p>0.1011011101111011111011111101111111…</p>
<p>It is irrational, infinitely long, and never repeats - however, you'd never find the sequence 1001 in there.</p>

