			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-914017">
									

<p>How did the Foundation discover that this 001-A was anomalous in the first place? It was acquired in 1980, before the microwave background pattern was discovered, and its only *obvious* anomalous characteristic is its indestructibility. For all that a vacationing Foundation staff member would be able to tell from viewing it on display, it'd just look like a particularly exquisite piece of ancient craftsmanship — or even a modern forgery, if he knew enough to be suspicious of the fine detail approaching the "lock".</p>

